        "subject": "LU-6055 hsm: improve error handling in sanity-hsm",
        "message": "LU-6055 hsm: improve error handling in sanity-hsm\n\nIn path2fid() propagate errors from 'lfs path2fid'.  In\nfile_creation_failure() redirect the output of df to stderr so that it\nis not captured by command substitution.\n\nThis is a backport to b2_5 of\nLustre change: http://review.whamcloud.com/13154\nLustre commit: 27f65af06d0906856041cbcf2537cfabe2a90583\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7fabf46af4aa36c6affef45cf8c9b044a7aa29dd\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n"
      },
